    "short_description": "KC's great urban park — trails, wildlife, and world-class outdoor theater.",
    "long_description": "Swope Park is one of the largest urban parks in the United States, sprawling across more than 1,700 acres on Kansas City's south side. It's a destination that rewards visitors of all kinds. Hikers and mountain bikers will find miles of well-maintained singletrack at the Wudchuk Run and Mountain Bike trailheads, winding through dense hardwood forest and creek drainages. \n\nFamilies can spend a full day at the Kansas City Zoo & Aquarium, home to hundreds of species across immersive habitats. As the sun goes down, the iconic Starlight Theatre — an open-air amphitheater nestled into the hillside — comes alive with Broadway productions and concerts under the Missouri sky. Swope Park is a rare place where a morning trail run and an evening show can share the same day.",
